   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject Two Hundred One KNOWING THAT YOU HAVE ETERNAL LIFE Scripture: 1 John 5:12, 13 The meaning of eternal life Eternal life is life that is eternal.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Eternal life is God s life.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Eternal life is in the Son of God God put His eternal life into His Son.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>He that has the Son of God has eternal life.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The proof of having eternal life You can know whether you have eternal life.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Emphasize that it is wrong if one does not know whether he has eternal life.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>The words of the Bible prove that we have eternal life.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Here it says, These things have I written unto you, that ye may know that ye have eternal life...</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Based upon the words of the Bible, one should know that he has eternal life.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>If one does not believe in God s word, he makes God a liar.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>We should reject our own feeling rather than disbelieve the words of the Bible; we should distrust ourselves rather than make God a liar.</S>
   </TEXT>
